{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17610466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17610466"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:01:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:01:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16173"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16173","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16173"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.07,0.02,0.64,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8864"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75100"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8864"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16173"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60607"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2333"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"},{"type":"tags","id":"10640"},{"type":"tags","id":"10653"},{"type":"tags","id":"10770"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21111"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21114"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75100"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBreastfeeding provides numerous health benefits for both mothers and infants that extend well beyond the period of lactation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a long-term health benefit of breastfeeding for both mother and infant?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reduced risk of type 2 diabetes","Decreased risk of osteoporosis","Lower blood pressure","Improved immune function","Reduced risk of allergies"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ereduced risk of type 2 diabetes\u003C/strong\u003E is a well-documented long-term benefit shared by both breastfeeding mothers and their breastfed infants. For mothers, lactation improves insulin sensitivity and glucose metabolism. For infants, breast milk contains bioactive compounds that influence metabolic programming.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent incomplete or incorrect associations:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased risk of osteoporosis\u003C/strong\u003E - While bone mineral density temporarily decreases during lactation, it typically returns to baseline after weaning\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELower blood pressure\u003C/strong\u003E - While some studies show modest effects in children, this benefit is not clearly demonstrated for mothers\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImproved immune function\u003C/strong\u003E - This primarily benefits the infant during the breastfeeding period rather than long-term\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced risk of allergies\u003C/strong\u003E - While breastfeeding may provide some protection against allergies in infants, this benefit is not demonstrated for mothers\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional maternal benefits include reduced risk of breast and ovarian cancer. Infants also experience improved cognitive development and reduced risk of various chronic diseases.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Breastfeeding reduces the risk of type 2 diabetes in both mothers and their children","Breastfeeding decreases the risk of breast and ovarian cancer in mothers","Breastfed infants have lower rates of obesity and improved cognitive development"],"references":["Gouveri E, Papanas N, Hatzitolios AI, Maltezos E. Breastfeeding and diabetes. Curr Diabetes Rev. 2011 Mar;7(2):135-42. doi: 10.2174/157339911794940684. PMID: 21348815.","Doughty KN, Taylor SN. Barriers and benefits to breastfeeding with gestational diabetes. Semin Perinatol. 2021 Mar;45(2):151385. doi: 10.1016/j.semperi.2020.151385. Epub 2020 Dec 31. PMID: 33446343.","Queensland Government. Importance of breastfeeding. Queensland Health. Available from: https://www.health.qld.gov.au/clinical-practice/guidelines-procedures/clinical-staff/maternity/nutrition/breastfeeding/importance","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60607"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16173"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60607"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T21:32:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T21:33:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8864"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75100"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"item